properties.areaDesc: Southern Lake/North Shore; Carlton/South St. Louis
properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 12 at 3:11AM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...HEAVY LAKE EFFECT SNOW AFFECTING DULUTH AND NORTH SHORE AREAS...

.Heavy lake effect snow bands continue to stream off Lake
Superior into the Duluth and North Shore areas early this morning.
The expectation is that the lake effect snow bands will continue
to pivot northward today as winds turn more east to southeasterly,
impacting the North Shore as far north as Lutsen and Tofte this
afternoon. Additional snowfall accumulations of between 2 to 4
inches are expected, but some heavier accumulations will be
possible if a more intense band of lake effect snow develops.

* WHAT...Heavy lake effect snow. Additional snow accumulations of
up to 4 inches will be possible for areas of southern Lake
county.

* WHERE...In Wisconsin, Douglas County. In Minnesota, Southern
Lake and Carlton and South St. Louis Counties. This includes
the Tribal Lands of the Fond du Lac Band.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions, and reduced
visibility at times.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1. Road
conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM CST EARLY THIS MORNING
